# tProc v2 Technical Manual (ISA & Architecture)

This document provides a comprehensive overview of the **tProc v2** (72-bit) architecture, designed for the QICK (Quantum Instrumentation Control Kit) platform.

---

## 1. Instruction Format (72-bit)

Each instruction is exactly 72 bits wide, divided into a **Header (16-bit)** and a **Payload (56-bit)**.

### Instruction Bit-Fields
| Bits | Field | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Header [71:56]** | | |
| 15:13 | `HEADER` | OpCode (3 bits): CFG, BRANCH, REG_WR, etc. |
| 12 | [AI](file:///e:/Homework_NU/winter_project/qick/qick_lib/qick/tprocv2_assembler.py#1874-1912) | Address Immediate Flag (1: IMM, 0: REG) |
| 11:10 | `DF` | Data Format (2 bits): 16-bit, 24-bit, 32-bit IMM support. |
| 9:7 | [COND](file:///e:/Homework_NU/winter_project/qick/qick_lib/qick/tprocv2_assembler.py#1147-1157) | Condition Code (3 bits): ALWAYS, EQ, LT, NZ, NS, FLAG, etc. |
| 6 | [SO](file:///e:/Homework_NU/winter_project/qick/qick_lib/qick/tprocv2_assembler.py#1202-1307) | Source Option / Type modifier. |
| 5 | `TO` | Time Option / Multi-function bit. |
| 4:0 | `UF/ALU` | Update Flag / ALU op (reduced set for fused instructions). |
| **Payload [55:0]** | | |
| 55:45 | `ADDR/rsA0` | Address 0 or Literal Address. |
| 44:39 | `rsA1` | Address Register 1. |
| 38:7 | `IMM / rsD` | 32-bit Immediate data or Dual source registers. |
| 6:0 | `RD` | Destination Register address (7 bits = 128 regs). |

---

## 2. Register Map

tProc v2 utilizes 128 addressable registers, categorized by their prefix/function:

### 2.1 Special Function Registers (sREG: `s0` - `s15`)
| Addr | Mnemonic | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `s0` | `zero` | Constant 0. |
| `s1` | `s_rand` | LFSR Random Number generator. |
| [s2](file:///e:/Homework_NU/winter_project/qick/qick_lib/qick/asm_v2.py#1721-1735) | `s_cfg` | Configuration and Control bits. |
| `s3` | `s_arith` | ALU lower 32-bit result (Arith IP). |
| `s4-s5` | `s_div` | Divider Quotient and Remainder. |
| `s10` | `s_status` | Processor status flags (Ready, New Data, etc.). |
| `s11` | `s_time` | Current User Time (Master Clock). |
| `s14` | `s_out_time` | Time used for the next output. |
| `s15` | [s_addr](file:///e:/Homework_NU/winter_project/qick/qick_lib/qick/asm_v2.py#2621-2637) | Current Program Counter (PC). |

### 2.2 Data Registers (dREG: `r0` - `r31`)
General-purpose 32-bit registers for user computation and variables.

### 2.3 Waveform Registers (wREG: `w0` - `w15`)
Specialized registers meant for pulse parameterization (Frequency, Phase, Envelope, etc.).

---

## 3. Instruction Set Architecture (ISA)

Basic OpCodes defined in [_qproc_defines.svh](file:///e:/Homework_NU/winter_project/qick/firmware/ip/qick_processor/src/_qproc_defines.svh):

| OpCode (3-bit) | Mnemonic | Primary Function |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `000` | [CFG](file:///e:/Homework_NU/winter_project/qick/qick_lib/qick/tprocv2_assembler.py#1494-1510) | Configure internal states or update flags. |
| `001` | [BRANCH](file:///e:/Homework_NU/winter_project/qick/qick_lib/qick/tprocv2_assembler.py#1511-1544) | Jump or Call based on condition. |
| `010` | `ARITH/CTRL` | Extended math (DSP blocks) or Peripheral control. |
| `100` | [REG_WR](file:///e:/Homework_NU/winter_project/qick/qick_lib/qick/tprocv2_assembler.py#1351-1439) | Standard register write (ALU, IMM, or MEM). |
| `101` | [MEM_WR](file:///e:/Homework_NU/winter_project/qick/qick_lib/qick/tprocv2_assembler.py#1440-1465) | Write to Data Memory or Wave Memory. |
| `110` | [PORT_WR](file:///e:/Homework_NU/winter_project/qick/qick_lib/qick/tprocv2_assembler.py#1545-1654) | **Fused Instruction**: Pulse output + Register write. |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Conditional Execution**: EVERY instruction in v2 can be conditional. By setting the [COND](file:///e:/Homework_NU/winter_project/qick/qick_lib/qick/tprocv2_assembler.py#1147-1157) field in the header, an instruction will only execute if the ALU flags or external triggers match the condition.

---

## 4. Pipeline Structure

tProc v2 implements a **5-stage pipeline**:
1. **Fetch**: Read instruction from PMEM.
2. **Decode**: Extract fields, check conditions, read register file.
3. **Ex1**: Address calculation and ALU Phase 1.
4. **Ex2**: Memory access or Port output.
5. **WriteBack**: Update registers with results.

---

## 5. Recommended Learning Path (RTL Files)

If you want to master the structure, read these RTL files in order:

1. **[_qproc_defines.svh](file:///e:/Homework_NU/winter_project/qick/firmware/ip/qick_processor/src/_qproc_defines.svh)**: The "Dictionary". Understand the structs and OpCode naming.
2. **[qcore_cpu.sv](file:///e:/Homework_NU/winter_project/qick/firmware/ip/qick_processor/src/qcore_cpu.sv)**: The "Brain". Focus on the `DECODER` logic (approx. Line 190) and the `PIPELINE` stages.
3. **[qcore_reg_bank.sv](file:///e:/Homework_NU/winter_project/qick/firmware/ip/qick_processor/src/qcore_reg_bank.sv)**: The "Memory". See how registers are muxed and how SFRs are mapped.
4. **[_qproc_ips.sv](file:///e:/Homework_NU/winter_project/qick/firmware/ip/qick_processor/src/_qproc_ips.sv)**: The "Tools". Deep dive into the `AB_alu` logic to see supported math ops.
5. **[tprocv2_assembler.py](file:///e:/Homework_NU/winter_project/qick/qick_lib/qick/tprocv2_assembler.py)**: The "Translator". See how high-level ASM maps to the 72-bit bitstream.
